### ── Direct user → document access ─────────────────────────────

### 1. Grant alice direct reader access to document 1
POST http://localhost:8080/admin/tuples
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user": "alice",
  "relation": "reader",
  "object_type": "document",
  "object_id": "1"
}

### 2. alice can view document 1 (200 OK)
GET http://localhost:8080/documents/1
X-User: alice

### 3. bob cannot view document 1 (403 Forbidden)
GET http://localhost:8080/documents/1
X-User: bob

### ── Indirect access: user → group → document ─────────────────

### 4. Add charlie as a member of the "engineering" group
POST http://localhost:8080/admin/tuples
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user": "charlie",
  "relation": "member",
  "object_type": "group",
  "object_id": "engineering"
}

### 5. Grant the engineering group reader access to document 2
POST http://localhost:8080/admin/tuples
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "group:engineering#member",
  "relation": "reader",
  "object_type": "document",
  "object_id": "2"
}

### 6. charlie can view document 2 via group membership (200 OK)
GET http://localhost:8080/documents/2
X-User: charlie

### 7. bob still cannot view document 2 (403 Forbidden)
GET http://localhost:8080/documents/2
X-User: bob
